parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Electrical System (NHTSA Campaign Number: 23V440000)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair for the electrical system may cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or loses motive power
warning lights illuminated on the instrument panel
message "Stop Safely Now" or "System Fault" displayed

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Telematics Control Unit (TCU) Failure and 3G to 4G Modem Upgrade Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Telematics Control Unit (TCU) can cause the GPS and location tracking system to malfunction, leaving the driver without access to safety systems in the event of a crash. The unannounced change from 3G to 4G modem can also render the vehicle's telecommunications system inoperable.
symptoms: The GPS and location tracking system no longer work
no access to safety systems in the event of a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-voltage battery can cause the check engine warning light to illuminate, potentially leading to a loss of power, reduced vehicle performance, and increased risk of stalling or breakdown, which can compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates on the instrument panel.
